A simple HTML/CSS version will make it easy to host the summary online while keeping the same calm tone and clear structure.  
Here’s a lightweight outline you can adapt for any website:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Grounding & Crisis‑Response Guide for Neurodiverse Support</title>
<style>
  body {
    font-family: "Open Sans", Lato, Verdana, sans-serif;
    background-color: #BACDB0;
    color: #202124;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  header {
    background-color: #497C78;
    color: #FFF;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.2em 0;
  }
  main {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 2em auto;
    padding: 0 1em;
    background-color: #FFF;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }
  h2 {
    color: #345875;
  }
  footer {
    background-color: #345875;
    color: #F7F7F7;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.8em;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
  a { color: #345875; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>Grounding & Crisis‑Response Guide for Neurodiverse Support</h1>
</header>

<main>
  <h2>Purpose</h2>
  <p>A community‑developed resource that teaches peers, caregivers, and educators how to use calm, sensory‑friendly language to support people experiencing extreme distress. It promotes safety, connection, and referral to professional or emergency help when needed.</p>

  <h2>What’s Included</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Five short grounding scripts for different crisis responses.</li>
    <li>Design and accessibility standards for print and digital use.</li>
    <li>Slide template and quick feedback form for trainings.</li>
    <li>Crisis resources: <strong>988 (U.S.)</strong>, <a href="https://findahelpline.com" target="_blank">findahelpline.com</a> (international).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Use & Sharing</h2>
  <p>This guide is licensed under <strong>CC BY‑NC 4.0</strong> and may be freely shared or adapted for non‑commercial educational purposes with attribution. It is not a clinical tool and should always be accompanied by up‑to‑date crisis contacts and professional‑care referrals.</p>

  <h2>Credits</h2>
  <p>Compiled by Community Mental‑Health Educators (2024). Review scheduled annually for language and resource accuracy.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Email: <a href="mailto:community-support@yourorg.org">community‑support@yourorg.org</a><br>
     Website: <a href="https://organization-site.org/groundingguide">organization‑site.org/groundingguide</a></p>

  <h2>Safety Note</h2>
  <p>If you ever feel unsafe with yourself or someone else, call or text <strong>988 (U.S.)</strong> or visit <a href="https://findahelpline.com" target="_blank">findahelpline.com</a> for worldwide options.</p>
</main>

<footer>
  © 2024 Community Mental‑Health Educators • CC BY‑NC 4.0
</footer>

</body>
</html>
```

This markup produces a clear, single‑page layout that’s readable on phones or desktops and highlights crisis‑resource links prominently.

